np.random.seed(42)
n_groups = 2
group_size = 20

data = {
    "group": np.repeat([f"Group {i + 1}" for i in range(n_groups)], group_size),
    "x": np.random.uniform(0, 10, n_groups * group_size),
    "z": np.random.normal(0, 1, n_groups * group_size),
}
In [6]:
data["y"] = (
    2.0  # Intercept
    + 0.5 * data["x"]  # Fixed effect of x
    + np.random.normal(0, 1, n_groups * group_size)  # Residual error
    + np.random.normal(0, 2, n_groups).repeat(group_size)  # Random intercept per group
)

# Create a DataFrame
df = pd.DataFrame(data)
df

# Visualization
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))

# Plot the data with group-specific random effects
sns.scatterplot(x="x", y="y", hue="group", data=df, palette="tab10", alpha=0.7)

# Add fixed-effect regression line
x_vals = np.linspace(df["x"].min(), df["x"].max(), 100)
y_vals = result.params["const"] + result.params["x"] * x_vals
plt.plot(x_vals, y_vals, color="black", linestyle="--", label="Fixed Effect")

# Add random effects
for group in df["group"].unique():
    random_effect = result.random_effects[group][0]  # Access the random intercept
    y_vals_group = result.params["const"] + result.params["x"] * x_vals + random_effect
    plt.plot(x_vals, y_vals_group, alpha=0.3, label=f"{group} Random Effect")

plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc="upper left")
plt.title("Linear Mixed Model Visualization")
plt.xlabel("x")
plt.ylabel("y")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.regression.mixed_linear_model import MixedLM
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load the dietox dataset
data = sm.datasets.get_rdataset("dietox", "geepack").data
data["Pig"] = data["Pig"].astype("category")
# Inspect the data
print(data.head())

# Fit a Linear Mixed Model
# Predict Weight based on Time (fixed effect) with a random intercept for each Pig
model = MixedLM(data["Weight"], sm.add_constant(data["Time"]), groups=data["Pig"])
result = model.fit()

# Display model summary
print(result.summary())

# Visualization
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))

# Scatterplot of Weight vs. Time for each Pig
sns.scatterplot(data=data, x="Time", y="Weight", hue="Pig", palette="tab20", alpha=0.6)

# Plot the fixed-effect line
x_vals = np.linspace(data["Time"].min(), data["Time"].max(), 100)
y_fixed = result.params["const"] + result.params["Time"] * x_vals
plt.plot(x_vals, y_fixed, color="black", linestyle="--", label="Fixed Effect")

# Add random effects for each Pig
for Pig in data["Pig"].cat.categories:
    random_effect = result.random_effects[Pig][0]  # Access the random intercept
    y_random = result.params["const"] + result.params["Time"] * x_vals + random_effect
    plt.plot(x_vals, y_random, alpha=0.4, label=f"Pig {Pig}")

plt.title("Linear Mixed Model: Weight vs. Time by Pig")
plt.xlabel("Time")
plt.ylabel("Weight")
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc="upper left", fontsize="small")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
